<subSubSection id="27C89EE4281D0F10FD7072948BC3FDC2" pageId="4" pageNumber="374" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="6F6DCD6F281D0F10FD7072948CF1FF03" blockId="4.[685,1173,193,560]" pageId="4" pageNumber="374">
<emphasis id="5DA6117D281D0F10FD7072948B3DFF25" bold="true" box="[709,838,194,215]" pageId="4" pageNumber="374">Distribution.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="A8D2B6EC281D0F10FCE672978BC1FF25" authorityName="PASCOE" authorityYear="1887" box="[851,954,193,215]" class="Insecta" family="Ripiphoridae" genus="Aporrhipis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="374" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5DA6117D281D0F10FCE672978BC1FF25" box="[851,954,193,215]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="374">Aporrhipis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from 
<collectingRegion id="AD16038D281D0F10FD18728A8B09FF03" box="[685,882,220,241]" country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso do Sul" pageId="4" pageNumber="374">Mato Grosso do Sul</collectingRegion>
(Corumbá) and 
<collectingRegion id="AD16038D281D0F10FBA7728A8C45FF03" box="[1042,1086,220,241]" country="Brazil" name="Para" pageId="4" pageNumber="374">Pará</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="17C58DFF281D0F10FBFC728A8CFDFF03" box="[1097,1158,220,241]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="374">Brazil</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6F6DCD6F281D0F10FD7072A18BC3FDC2" blockId="4.[685,1173,193,560]" pageId="4" pageNumber="374">
<emphasis id="5DA6117D281D0F10FD7072A18B7FFEFE" bold="true" box="[709,772,247,268]" pageId="4" pageNumber="374">Notes.</emphasis>
<materialsCitation id="DFBAC732281D0F10FCB872A18BCFFDC2" county="Therefore" location="The" municipality="After" pageId="4" pageNumber="374" specimenCount="2" typeStatus="holotype">
<bibRefCitation id="0B43B09E281D0F10FCB872A18BE3FEFE" author="Pascoe, F. P." box="[781,920,247,268]" pageId="4" pageNumber="374" pagination="8 - 20" refId="ref2886" refString="Pascoe, F. P. 1887. Notes on Coleoptera, with descriptions of new genera and species - Part VI. The Annals and Magazine of Natural History 20: 8 - 20." type="journal article" year="1887">Pascoe (1887)</bibRefCitation>
states in the original description that he saw only a ‘unique specimen’, and thus this specimen (now in The Natural History Museum) is a 
<typeStatus id="B06973CD281D0F10FC9B73108BFBFEA9" box="[814,896,326,347]" pageId="4" pageNumber="374">holotype</typeStatus>
. The genitalia drawings herein are of the 
<typeStatus id="B06973CD281D0F10FCB173378B2DFE84" box="[772,854,353,374]" pageId="4" pageNumber="374">holotype</typeStatus>
. 
<location id="6A0D9BB4281D0F10FCE873378BFAFE84" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:E77B7C79281B0F10FCB7704F8BC3FDC2:6A0D9BB4281D0F10FCE873378BFAFE84" box="[861,897,353,374]" county="Therefore" municipality="After" name="The" pageId="4" pageNumber="374">The</location>
only other known specimen of the genus, from the 
<location id="6A0D9BB4281D0F10FCCC732D8A89FE59" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:E77B7C79281B0F10FCB7704F8BC3FDC2:6A0D9BB4281D0F10FCCC732D8A89FE59" county="Therefore" municipality="After" name="Carnegie Museum of Natural History" pageId="4" pageNumber="374">Carnegie Museum of Natural History</location>
, appears to be conspecific. 
<location id="6A0D9BB4281D0F10FC5773C08B8BFE59" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:E77B7C79281B0F10FCB7704F8BC3FDC2:6A0D9BB4281D0F10FC5773C08B8BFE59" box="[994,1008,406,427]" county="Therefore" municipality="After" name="It" pageId="4" pageNumber="374">It</location>
was dissected and the genitalia removed before it came into our hands. 
<collectingMunicipality id="8F095715281D0F10FD18739D8AA7FE12" box="[685,732,459,480]" pageId="4" pageNumber="374">After</collectingMunicipality>
careful examination of the vial attached to the specimen, we did not find the genitalia, and they must be considered lost. 
<collectingCounty id="860CB5E3281D0F10FCEC70568BCFFDE7" box="[857,948,512,533]" pageId="4" pageNumber="374">Therefore</collectingCounty>
, its conspecificity cannot be established with certainty
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
